                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-08T22:00:00+03:06"
                            >November 8, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>175. Following telegram has been sent to the Legation at Cairo.</p>
                <p>152, November 8, 9 p.m. Following for General Royce. In reply to your telegram
                    154, November 6, 4 p.m.: “The King has indicated that he will be pleased to
                    receive you and Military Mission in Jidda December 12.”</p>
                <p>Repeated to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
